                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.00111 Armament Control/878: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-06-04T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 4, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>266. Your 352, May 17, noon. The Department appreciates the difficulties involved
                    in your obtaining accurate detailed information regarding the military
                    situation, but it would appreciate receiving from time to time such reports on
                    current developments as may help to throw light upon the subject discussed in
                    its 211, May 9, 4 p.m. Information as to extent to which Italian control has
                    been extended over Ethiopian territory would be particularly helpful.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
